---
title: Steak with Mushroom Cream Sauce plus Roasted Potatoes & Carrots
description: Our ranch steak has such a deep, rich, and gloriously meaty flavor that it could be a stand-alone dish with little more than salt and pepper for seasoning. Still, we’re adding top-notch sides and a full-bodied sauce to this recipe so that it soars above and beyond. Crispy roasted potatoes and tender roasted carrots make it filling and hearty, while the mushroom pan sauce that’s spooned on top has savory complexity. Are you drooling yet? We’re pretty confident this steak dinner will more than meat your expectations.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6231f2c98cae5f6cde4c6187-1cfdad77.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/steak-with-mushroom-cream-sauce-6231f2c98cae5f6cde4c6187-702b93fc.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/steak-with-mushroom-cream-sauce-6231f2c98cae5f6cde4c6187
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 960 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and bottom positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel, and cut
@Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice
@Button Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and
mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon};
season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of olive oil; season with salt and
pepper.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and carrots
> on bottom rack.

While veggies roast, heat a drizzle of olive oil and @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a
large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally,
until golden brown and slightly crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and
pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, pat @Ranch Steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously
all over with salt and pepper.

Once mushrooms are done, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan
over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes}
per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil and @Butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over
medium-high heat.

Add garlic and scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}.

Bring to a simmer, then stir in mushrooms and any resting juices from steak;
cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} until smooth. Season with
salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, potatoes, and carrots between plates. Spoon pan sauce over steak.
Garnish with scallion greens and serve.